cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper proposes an algorithm for automated detection of polyps in colon capsule endoscopy videos. This involves analyzing the geometrical and texture content of the frames in the video sequence. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as these are the areas that deal with image analysis and classification. Additionally, the use of statistical performance evaluation suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of digital cameras and video sequences suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
